{"Body":"<p>According to Diana Archangeli (1997) there is a universal set of constraints (CON) that is part of our innate knowledge of language. These constraints are used in Optimality Theory, such as NOCODA: 'syllables end with a vowel'. </p>\n\n<p>Is there a formal list of such constraints, or are there too many to list/not enough information about them?</p>\n", "Id":"3599", "LastEditorUserId":"444", "Title":"What is the universal set of constraints in Optimality Theory?", "CreationDate":"2013-04-22T13:11:42.877", "OwnerUserId":"783", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<phonology><optimality-theory>", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2013-04-23T13:51:21.580", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"127", "WebsiteUrl":"", "Location":"Netherlands", "Id":"444", "DownVotes":"2", "AccountId":"902812", "Views":"19", "Reputation":"934", "CreationDate":"2011-10-23T14:14:27.380", "DisplayName":"arjan", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-14T14:07:55.473", "AboutMe":""}, "ViewCount":"115", "LastActivityDate":"2013-04-23T13:51:21.580", "Score":"4", "CommentCount":"3", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"133", "WebsiteUrl":"http://None", "Id":"783", "AccountId":"1263184", "CreationDate":"2012-02-20T12:40:45.587", "AboutMe":"<p>English Language graduate.</p>\n", "Age":"24", "Location":"Wales", "DownVotes":"2", "Views":"16", "Reputation":"1036", "DisplayName":"Danger Fourpence", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-16T19:41:06.517"}}